{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a71417cc3fb48d6866a", "type": "numerical", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba5"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "648b5a3a0d9d0b909f7b6494", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "The radius of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>2</mn><mi>nd</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;orbit of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>He</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;of Bohr&#39;s model is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;and that of fourth orbit of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>Be</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;is represented as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;Now the ratio&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;The value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;is _____.", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "2", "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p>The formula to calculate the radius&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mi>r</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;of any&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>n</mi><mi>th</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;Bohr&#39;s orbit is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfrac><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>Z</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;is Bohr&#39;s radius,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>&nbsp;is the principal quantum number and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Z</mi></math>&nbsp;is the atomic number.</p><p>Thus, for Helium ion,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfrac><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>And, for the Beryllium ion,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfrac><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Divide equation (3) by equation (2) to obtain the required ratio.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ17346151", "numericalLowerLimit": 2, "numericalUpperLimit": 2, "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["6160244defc76de5773f3b04", "6160244db8c481525a1215ef", "6160244cb4f517cc680aa439", "61964c95f3d02062bde4be67", "61e7bd7f77a4ea0f853aa953", "6160244b2069b4ac8ab389b4", "61c089b72898f7e4ea712965", "6160244ea9c7f3586ff3388b", "61bb822a5f69d75f5f0ee9ea", "61964c95f72a9436d4897955", "629109eac170f867f214b337", "629f3a8f9b4bccc32c98f80b", "62962120a7c7723b8f219be5", "629f390a8f471e20494d559a", "64eb06f73118f713ecfef2ab", "66d5856ba75f05ee8564f74b", "67921d8e1d5b5072da5e9c11", "67fdff50378e1624ea7b6a0a", "6809202c3a10446a207fdef1"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}